      "body" : "The only sensible change to the Bitcoin amount protocol would be to make them a proper fraction instead of an integer, not to simply buy a few more years by multiplying by ten or a hundred. Given that, Bitcoin would be infinitely divisible in both decimal and tonal, and people could trade sizes like 1/3 or 1/7 which are completely impossible right now.\r\n\r\nIf Tonal users alone aren't considered \"significant\", then I could try adding Dozenal support too... DSA at least seems to have a more organized online presence.",
